@zhangguanzhang thank you for replay. I re-run failed and skipped tests. probably I should not start optional release test, sorry for that.

So, what should I do now?

@TomSweeneyRedHat  I write some comments to your reviews. I switched docker to podman nowadays. I use OSX development and remote servers for containers. After this switch lots of my docker builds started to fail. It's not about parameters/arguments. I am ok with that. However podman does not handle context dir and containerfile as docker handles it. 

I also asked, however I didnot get an answer about tihs question too: the **-f** parameter of docker build reads file contents and sends it to the remote side. hence this behavior allows developers to symlink dockerfile to outside contextdir. It's ok to know that podman will support it or not. However I didnot get an answer too.

Lot's of things are unclear. Hence I do not know what should I do. I need a image build tool whose behaviors are identical to dockers'. The aim of podman is that or not?
